{title: Let My Life Be A Light}
{artist: Doyle Lawson}
{composer: unknown}

[G]Let me live blessed Lord in the [C]light of Thy [G]word
Let my life be a light on a [D7]hill
Leading [G]souls now astray to the [C]straight narrow [G]way
Help me do some good deed [D7]while I [G]live
Let my [C]life be a light shining [G]out through the night
May I help struggling ones to the [D7]fold
Spreading [G]cheer everywhere to the [C]sad and the [G]lone
Let my life be a [D7]light to some [G]soul
Give me wisdom and power every[C]day every [G]hour
Let me drink from the fountain [D7]above
Guide my [G]footsteps awry through the [C]dark stormy [G]night
Give me peace give me [D7]joy give me [G]love
Repeat #2
Give me souls for my hire let my [C]life be on [G]fire
Shining out to the world as a [D7]guide
Help me [G]rescue someone sinking [C]now with no [G]hope
That in heaven we shall [D7]ever a[G]bide
Repeat #2